#Text=The New Orleans Pelicans ( 3 - 11 ) defeated the Phoenix Suns ( 7 - 6 ) 122 - 116 on Sunday .
#Text=This was an extremley high - scoring game and it was simply fun to watch , Both teams had well over 100 possessions in the game and the pace was at a ridiculously high level .
#Text=There were also a ton of three - pointers taken , as both teams attempted a combined 66 threes .
#Text=The biggest difference in the game was the shooting , as the Pelicans shot 46 percent while the Suns shot just 39 percent from the field .
#Text=The Suns played good enough to win in this game , but they simply didn’t shoot well enough to keep up with the Pelicans .
#Text=Their defense was lacking as well , as they allowed twice as many paint points as they scored ( 44 - 22 ) .
#Text=Eric Bledsoe put in another all - around great performance though , as he tallied 29 points , seven rebounds and six assists in the defeat .
#Text=He did miss the majority of the third quarter for an unknown injury , but he was able to return for the final 12 minutes .
#Text=An interesting development is that of Tyson Chandler’s playing time , as he saw just 16 minutes in the defeat .
#Text=His minutes have been slowly dissipating as of late and it 's mainly due to the fact that the Suns prefer to play small - ball .
#Text=It will be interesting to see how this Chandler experiment will work in Phoenix .
#Text=The Suns will have to play again on Monday in the second half of a back - to - back , as they 'll have to travel to San Antonio to take on the Spurs .
#Text=The Pelicans appear to be finally putting it all together and it 's likely as simple as health .
#Text=Anthony Davis played a full complement of minutes here and had a fantastic game .
#Text=Davis totaled 32 points , 19 rebounds , four blocks and two steals in the victory .
#Text=The bench also continued its recent success , as Ish Smith and Ryan Anderson put in some fine performances .
#Text=In fact , Anderson had 29 points and that 's his fourth consecutive 20 - point game , which is a fantastic sign considering he had just seven 20 - point outings all of last season .
#Text=Smith flirted with a triple - double , as he collected 17 points , nine rebounds and eight assists off the bench .
#Text=This is a very talented team and they are still feared no matter how bad their record looks .
#Text=The Pelicans have now won two - straight and they 'll look to add to that winning streak on Wednesday in a rematch with these Suns .
